<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="108f6f27-53e1-40b8-b3ad-c5b8e661e722" >

    <h2>Key dates for Viola Desmond Student Bursary&nbsp;</h2> 
<ul> 
 <li>September 23, 2020: Bursary applications open&nbsp;</li> 
 <li>November 6, 2020: Bursary application closes</li> 
 <li>December 2020: Bursary applicant notified and issued</li> 
 <li>March 1, 2021: Bursary acknowledgement at the 13th annual Viola Desmond Awards Ceremony</li> 
</ul> 
<h2>About the Student Bursary&nbsp;</h2> 
<p>All applications to the Viola Desmond Bursary are considered, evaluated and awarded by the Black History Awareness Committee.</p> 
<p>The recipient is awarded $1,000.</p> 
<h3>Eligibility criteria&nbsp;</h3> 
<p>The bursary applicant must:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Self-identify as a woman.</li> 
 <li>Self-identify as Black, African Canadian or have Black/African Canadian ancestry.</li> 
 <li>Be currently enrolled as a student at Ryerson and have clear academic standing (minimum 1.67 cumulative grade point average is required for consideration).</li> 
 <li>Be a positive role model and advocate of the Black/African Canadian community.</li> 
 <li>Have demonstrated involvement in the community through extracurricular activities both on campus and/or in the community.</li> 
</ul>
    
